  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, that is correct. Money laundering is indeed illegal. It is the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (often referred to as \"dirty money\") appear legal (or \"clean\"). This typically involves disguising the origins of money obtained from criminal activities, such as drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption, by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions.\n\nThe illegality of money laundering is recognized internationally, and most countries have laws and regulations in place to combat it. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines and significant prison sentences. Financial institutions and other entities are often required to implement strict anti-money laundering (AML) policies and procedures to detect and prevent such activities.",
